<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Canada
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Toronto market bucked the trend in New York and posted solid gains in
moderate trading as bargain hunters shrugged off caution ahead of the
release of today's crucial US employment figures.
In spite of a slight decline by bonds, Canadian stocks built on Wednesday's
late rally, taking back some of the losses from the previous two days of
trading that shaved more than 90 points off the TSE 300 composite index.
The TSE 300 finished 22.96 points up at 4,276.32, while rises led declines
by 367 to 350 after volume of 60.3m shares valued at CDollars 889m.
Thirteen of the 14 sub-indices were up, with real estate, golds,
transportation and financial services leading the way. The paper and
forestry sector posted a decline.
