FT  07 OCT 94 / International Company News: CSR expects ADollars 100m from
pension surplus
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CSR, the Australian sugar and building products group, announced yesterday
that it expects to receive a ADollars 100m (USDollars 73.50m) cash transfer
early next year as a result of the surplus in its superannuation fund.
The company said that the fund had an actuarial surplus of ADollars 290m
when it was last valued. Accordingly, after 12 months of negotiation, it has
been decided that CSR will enjoy one third of this; that a further ADollars
100m will be used to improve fund members' benefits; and that the remaining
surplus will stay in the fund 'to maintain a buffer'.
CSR will treat the bonus - on which it will pay tax - as an abnormal item in
its next profit and loss statement.
