<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hoechst, the German chem-icals multinational, expects 1994 net profit to be
up 'more than 20 per cent', said Mr Gunter Metz, vice-chairman in charge of
US operations, AP-DJ reports from Mexico City.
'But that's still not enough,' he added, saying the company continued to
have problems worldwide in fibre and polymer sales.
