FT  07 OCT 94 / International Company News: Pargesa falls 6.6% to SFr105m in
first half
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Pargesa, the Swiss investment group controlled by the Belgian financier Mr
Albert Frere and Canada's Mr Paul Desmarais, reported consolidated net
earnings of SFr104.8m (Dollars 81.80m) in the first half, down 6.6 per cent,
mainly because of the rise of the Swiss franc.
Most of the group's industrial and financial holdings are based in Belgian
and French francs.
Petrofina's contribution was up 36 per cent to BFr5.2bn (Dollars 153m) and
that of the Tractabel utility advanced 2.8 per cent to BFr6.48bn.
The Royale Belge Insurance group raised its contribution 2.9 per cent to
BFr4.58bn while that of Banque Brussels Lambert was up 26 per cent to
BFr3.85bn.
Paribas, the main French holding, raised its contribution 13 per cent to
FFr1.27bn (Dollars 227m).
