The railways business in particular was suffering from falling prices caused
by over-capacity. It had booked 12 per cent more new orders in the period to
the end of August, but still needed to close one of its four German plants
and reduce its workforce by a third.
Overall order intake rose 1 per cent in the period, confirming the ZVEI
industry association's recent complaint that German electrical and
electronics companies had yet to benefit from the economic recovery.
