FT  07 OCT 94 / Ministry to make checks on lettuces
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Ministry of Agriculture will take random samples of lettuces this winter
to monitor the use of fungicides.
The move follows a report by a government working party which showed that 26
per cent of lettuces surveyed last year contained unacceptable pesticide
residues, an increase from 17 per cent the previous season. The Department
of Health has said the residues pose no risk to human health.
