<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 94 / Walker judge starts to sum up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MASON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The judge in the trial of Mr George Walker, the former chairman of the Brent
Walker group, yesterday warned the jury that fraud on a company was not a
'victimless' crime, John Mason writes.
Beginning his summing up, Judge Geoffrey Rivlin said the money at issue
sometimes came from shareholders, who were entitled to expect a company's
accounts to be honest.
The prosecution claims that Mr Walker and Mr Wilfred Aquilina, a former
Brent Walker finance director, fraudulently boosted the company's profits in
1984-89.
The two men deny charges of theft, false accounting and conspiring to
falsify accounts. The judge's summing-up will continue until October 17.
