to transactions with companies to determine charges, a Bank supervisor said
yesterday.
Mr David Holt, the Bank's senior manager of supervision and surveillance,
said it 'never loses the opportunity' to tell banks that capital rules were
not designed to deliver an accurate measure of risk in a single transaction.
'The banks nevertheless continue to use them for this purpose,' he said.
