<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 94 / Kurdish MPs stand trial
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN BARHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ANKARA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The treason trial of six pro-Kurdish former MPs resumes today in an Ankara
security court where prosecutors will continue reading their 400-page
indictment and presenting evidence to the judges. But the government now
says the six may stand for re-election in December in by-elections called to
fill their vacant seats. The six were arrested in March after the Turkish
constitutional court dissolved their DEP party and lifted their
parliamentary immunity. They are accused of membership of the outlawed PKK
Kurdish Workers party and plotting against the state. The charges carry the
death sentence.
