<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 94 / Greek 'spies' lose appeal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TIRANA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
An Albanian appeals court yesterday upheld guilty verdicts on five
ethnic-Greek minority leaders convicted of spying for Athens but reduced
their jail sentences for reasons of clemency. The move failed to appease the
Greek government, which called their original trial a political farce. The
five were arrested last April after Greek-speaking gunmen killed two
Albanian soldiers in a conscript camp near the border. Since their trial
began in August, Greece has vetoed an Ecu35m (Pounds 27.54m) loan to
Albania, effectively sealed its border and sent back about 70,000 illegal
Albanian immigrants.
