<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 94 / Economic Watch: Danish unemployment falls
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Denmark's unemployment rate in August fell to 12.2 per cent of the workforce
compared with 12.5 per cent in July, according to figures released yesterday
by Danmarks Statistik, the Danish national statistics agency. The figure was
in line with market expectations which predicted a drop in unemployment
levels on the back of a general improvement in the economy and the
introduction of new government training schemes. Total Danish retail sales
for July and August rose 4 per cent compared with a year earlier. Industrial
production, meanwhile, was up 11 per cent in August on last year.
Unemployment in the European Union was unchanged at 10.7 per cent, or about
17.2m, in August compared with a year ago, the European Commission's
statistical office Eurostat said yesterday. Spain had the highest
unemployment rate: 21.8 per cent.
