<TEXT>
Private buyers appear to be deserting the new car market in growing numbers,
although buoyant fleet business is keeping it above last year's levels,
according to figures released yesterday
Registration of new cars in September totalled 144,998, a 6.54 per cent
increase on the same month a year ago, said the Society of Motor
Manufacturers and Traders.  But registrations to private buyers were down by
4.6 per cent.
