FT  06 OCT 94 / IMF/World Bank: Low labour mobility hits Russia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Regional unemployment levels in Russia, from 1 to 11 per cent of the
workforce, are likely to become entrenched because of low labour mobility, a
World Bank report says, David Goodhart writes. The national unemployment
rate is 5-6 per cent, as opposed to the official rate of 2 per cent, but the
duration of unemployment is found to be short. In 1993, 60-80 per cent of
those leaving unemployment did so within four months.
