<HEADLINE>
FT  06 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Cananda
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sell orders and rising bond yields sent the Toronto market tumbling
yesterday morning, but the afternoon rally on Wall Street helped the TSE
retrieve some of the early loss in a day of heavy trading.
At its worst the TSE 300 index was down 58 points, but ended a net 20.9 off
at 4,253.36. Declines outscored rises by 209 to 480 after volume of 67.1m
shares valued at CDollars 1.07bn.
