FT  06 OCT 94 / Observer: Mum's the word
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Close-knit family, the Kennedys, even when divorcing. Joan Kennedy has just
postponed - until after elections on November 8 - a court action aimed at
reopening her 1982 divorce settlement with Senator Edward Kennedy.
She hasn't said why, and nor will her lawyer, Monroe Inker, say if the two
have met recently. 'I have been sworn to silence by my client,' says Inker.
Can it be that Kennedy, who has been a Democrat senator for 32 years, is
facing an unusually tough fight from Republican Mitt Romney, a venture
capitalist and son of former Michigan governor, George Romney?
